<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="material">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue  plinth</rs></rs> (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.70</measure> x  <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre" precision="circa">0.15</measure>)</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> along the front in one line.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p>Letters irregular, deeply cut (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.07</measure>).</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notAfter="0399" notBefore="0201">third-4th centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)
</p>
</div>

<div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w>  <w lemma="βουλή">Βουλὴ</w>  <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w>  <w lemma="δῆμος">Δῆμ<supplied reason="lost">ον</supplied></w>  </ab>
</div>

<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds)</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>The Council (set up a statue of) the People</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The Demos also dedicated a statue of the Council (<xref type="inscription" n="816" href="020101">2.101</xref>). The lettering might suggest a late antique date; but if these texts were inscribed by the sculptors, and not by professional letterers the argument is not strong. </p>
<p>For another statue of Demos see <xref type="inscription" n="1268" href="080052">8.52</xref> (=70.1023)</p>
</div>

